(7, 'listening', 'Light Pollution Research Proposal', 'Hi Professor, thanks for meeting me. Of course. What''s up? I''m drafting a proposal on reducing light pollution in campus housing. Great topic. What''s your first action plan? Conduct light measurements in dorm courtyard areas. Good. What tools will you use? A light meter app and handheld lux sensors. Reliable. Will you include student surveys? Yes—to assess awareness and attitudes. Excellent. What research question are you asking? Can shielding and reduced light intensity improve wildlife and sleep quality? Strong question. How will you test human effects? Survey residents before and after light adjustments. Good design. Any hypothesis? Yes: residents near shielded lighting report better sleep. Clear and measurable. Do I need a control site? Yes—an unmodified courtyard as comparison. Will lighting be changed in winter? Best in spring to avoid seasonal sleep variability. What about sharing results? Present at student sustainability forum. That''d be great. Anything else? No, thanks. Good luck with your project!', 4, 190, 'conversation', 'listening/t7c1.mp3'),

